The Kaduna State has announced that it will implement the new national minimum wage from September 2019. <img class="size-full wp-image-1236508 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=640%2C389&#038;ssl=1" alt="El-rufai kaduna state Governor" width="640" height="389" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=300%2C182&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=768%2C466&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=1024%2C622&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=58%2C35&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=260%2C158&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=200%2C121&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?resize=560%2C340&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-rufai.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> A statement signed by Muyiwa Adekeye, the Special Adviser to the governor on Media and Publicity said the decision was taken today at the state executive council meeting. ” The Kaduna State Executive Council today approved that payment of the new national minimum wage and consequential adjustments to civil servants will begin from 1st September 2019. Also read: N30,000 new minimum wage to be fully implemented ― Buhari “The Executive Council meeting, chaired by Dr Hadiza Balarabe, the Deputy Governor, noted the commitment of Governor Nasir El-Rufai to strengthen the public service and its capacity to deliver quality and responsive public service. The council deliberated on the minimum wage memo and unanimously approved commencement of the implementation in September 2019″ he said. Details shortly… Vanguard IT is certainly not the best of times for most states of the country. A host of them are on a cliff hanger over how to resolve the lingering industrial disharmony over the N18,000 minimum wage. Some of them like Adamawa, Enugu, Kano and Ebonyi have been paralysed by workers… September 15, 2011 In "Politics" ABUJA— AFTER two days of exchanging brick-bats regarding the 2019 presidential poll, President Muhammadu Buhari met and shook hands with former President Olusegun Obasanjo, yesterday, on a day the National Council of State approved N27,000 as minimum wage for states and the private sector and the Federal Government saying it… January 23, 2019 In "News" Even before the committee was announced, Labour had made its demand known as early as 2016. While the NLC and TUC initially demanded N56, 500, ULC demanded N96, 000 September 30, 2018 In "Special Report"